Just what I wanted.  MORE bloody exp.  The hope - the one little hope i had of one day making 60 - is now pretty much gone.  I have school to attend to.  I have friends.  Surprisingly enough, there's life outside Everquest (No matter how much I furvently try and deny it) and it's now just beginning to drag.<br>
<br>
What were Verant exactly trying to do?<br>
They've been obviously trying to appeal to the new players, thus making the younger levels much easier, and yet they seem to be intent on shafting the higher level community that has swelled over the last years.  I used to enjoy the 40's to early 50's...it was decent exp, you had to put <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> time</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> into it, but it wasn't the kind of exp that you'd go on for 3 hours and look back, and have 3 blues.  Nowadays i'll sit there plowing away in FG and find, egads, half a blue.<br>
<br>
