I was under the impression that they were moving exp out of 59 and 54 and sticking them in the levels below them.  That would make the exp needed to level a more smoother transition.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
On &quot;Penalty Level&quot; Rebalancing (Levels 51, 54, and 59): <br>
<br>
- Many people saw much smaller experience gains at level 60. This was due to the &quot;penalty level&quot; rebalancing effect more than anything that was done to NPC experience values. <br>
<br>
- In the previous patch, Level 60 became a full level, when it had been half a half level the day before. <br>
<br>
- &quot;Penalty levels&quot; have once again been rebalanced such that level 60 is much closer to the half level that it was before, and experience was instead redistributed throughout the earlier levels. <br>
<br>
- The penalty effect is still mostly mitigated, however the distribution should be more fair to those who are already level 60, yet do not have a full bar in that level. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm assuming they mean &quot;hell levels&quot; and not &quot;penalty levels&quot;.<br>
The levels listed in the patch message are hell levels.<br>
<br>
Hell Level: A level requireing more exp then average to get thru.<br>
<br>
Penalty Level: A level following a hell level.  You lose more exp on average becuase the exp you lose is based on the exp you needed to get on the previous level.<br>
<br>
For example, 59 is a hell level becuase it takes forever to get thru.   60 is a penalty level becuase you lose over 3 blues of exp when you die.<br>
<br>
I personally don't think any level 60 will complain about not getting much exp to put into level 60.  Level 60s don't need to level, becuase they can't anymore.  The only exp they need in level 60 is buffer exp.<br>
<br>
It sounds like they are doing their exp rebalancing calculations based on the beginning of level 50 to the end of 60, when they should be doing it on the beginning of level 50 to the beginning of level 60. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uelysianaheathertoes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElysianaHeathertoes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/6/02 7:07:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=725.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmm</span><hr size=1> Looks like VI had a chance to think about it, and gave us back some of the xp on lower lvl mobs, and seem to have worked out the resist trouble a little. This is good, all I was askin for, so woohoo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ustylina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stylina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/6/02 8:24:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=725.topic&index=65>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Oh, wonderful...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lol, ohhhhhh, the irony...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
