<br>
The agro increasing and decreasing spells are extremly useful in both xping in difficult locations and on raids.  <br>
<br>
On a raid, keeping agro buff on the MT means that other classes can do more damage without gaining agro, and by having a second enchanter cast on the next tank in the switch occasionally, tank switches become much more smooth.  In single group action, agro buff cast before tashing/slowing can and will save your ass (A good example is camping key parts in ssra).<br>
<br>
The deagro buff is very useful to be cast on a wizards.  It gives them a roughly 20% ability to nuke more (actually 1-[.9/1.1]), which in a 15 minute fight such as THO can result in a huge increase in damage output.<br>
<br>
Also, from what I've heard reported, the new sk agro spells affect the rampage list as well as the agro list.  That 6% increase can mean a huge difference on a mob like Arch Lich Rhag'Zhadune.<br>
<br>
Seranis <p><CENTER>
