</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ustylina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stylina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/10/02 9:25:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=725.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Oh, wonderful...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> On a raid, keeping agro buff on the MT means that other classes can do more damage without gaining agro,<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This hasn't really been an issue for us in NB- course, nearly all our warrior mains have bocs. We usually only lose melee when they get riposted below 40% or didn't put the proc'ing weapon away, (in which case the problem is with the melee who got killed, not the MT's performance) or after the MT died and the next tank hasn't gotten aggro yet. (I've thrown an aggro buff or two around in these situations, but my initial reaction was that it didn't help much)  This may change in the future, but with our current raids, aggro buffs are fairly redundant.<br>
<br>
In xp groups, while it would be nice to help the tank get aggro faster, I just don't have enough spell slots, and the fact that I have to recast it before every fight definitely reduces its effectiveness.<br>
<br>
I wasn't aware of how the aggro spells interacted with rampage- looks promising, though I'm somewhat wary of casting aggro increasing buffs on anyone but the MT. (although, watching bards and ranjurs die from rampage is lots of fun, and I wouldn't want to lose such pure glee on raids <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Also, in my experience, wizards are more limited by their manapools and/or the duration of the fight than by aggro.  Coordinating your chanters and wizards together to get a smooth aggro reduction buff working is more trouble than I'm willing to go through.  Maybe in the future, (ie, when NB gets enough emp keys, though I imagine we'll aim the aggro reduction buffs at clerics rather than wizzies...) but at this point, we gain too little benefit from it.<br>
<br>
That being said, I use the self-only aggro reduction buff religiously before tashing on raid mobs, and have put a few AA points into the innate aggro reduction. (slightly OT- do the aggro reduction buffs and AA skills stack?) <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<img src="http://personalpages.bellsouth.net/v/i/vincecrs/stylina.jpg"> </img>
<br>
Stylina, Phantasmist of the Rathe</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=725.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=725.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=725.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showPrevMessage?topicID=725.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=725.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=725.topic&index=69><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=725.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.threadControl?topicID=725.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=725.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=725.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub6.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><